  "title": "Insolvency and Restructuring Associate",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles & Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Execution of day-to-day issues on restructuring and insolvency projects</li><li>Liaison with stakeholders, creditors and other advisors</li><li>Assist in preparation of letters, notices, reports and presentation slides</li><li>Reconstruction of (complex) accounting records from incomplete information</li><li>Adjudication of creditors’ claims</li><li>Undertaking investigative work for the benefit of recovering assets for the insolvent estate</li><li>Attending meetings and assist in preparation of minutes of meetings</li><li>Undertaking company analysis, including financial modelling if required</li><li>Attending to statutory and compliance matters</li><li>Ad-hoc duties</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in Accountancy, ACCA or equivalent professional qualifications</li><li>Candidates with 1 year of audit experience in PAC firms and keen to specialize in Insolvency & Restructuring may apply</li><li>3 years of working experiences as above will be considered for Senior position</li><li>Able to work independently and in a team, to manage the project and meet project deadlines</li><li>Strong business acumen and logical thinking and analytical skills</li><li>Good written and spoken English and interpersonal skills</li></ul>",
